commentary: Usman Shinwari to Masvaure, OUT Usman Khan has Masvaure nicking off for 1. Umpire Gould raises his finger and sends the debutant back. This was on a back of a length and wide outside off, Masvaure is rooted to the crease as he chases after it and snicks it behind to the keeper. Poor shot, another poor start for Zimbabwe. All-new game, same-old story

commentary: Ngarava to Fakhar Zaman, FOUR runs fetches the pull from way outside off again, gets it away towards deep midwicket where there's a misfield to give away a boundary. Should have been no more than two

commentary: Ngarava to Fakhar Zaman, FOUR runs in his swinging arc, belted through midwicket. Game, set and match. Pakistan win with 241 balls to spare. This has been a hiding of the kind Zimbabwe haven't witnessed so far in the series. Pakistan seal the series 3-0
